President Obama and his wife, Michelle, send their greetings to Muslims worldwide on the occasion of Eid al-Adha and offer their congratulations to those performing Hajj. They acknowledge the participation of thousands of Muslim Americans in the pilgrimage to Mecca. They also highlight the significance of Eid al-Adha as a time to remember Abraham's willingness to sacrifice his son and the importance of distributing food to the less fortunate. The President mentions the United States' and international community's relief efforts in the Horn of Africa and Turkey. He emphasizes the shared roots and the role of faith in motivating communities to serve those in need. The President extends his best wishes for the Hajj season, saying "Eid Mubarak and Hajj Mabrour."